Package: CellSweeper
Title: Cluster-Aware Spatial QC for Single-Cell Resolution Transcriptomics
Version: 0.99.0
Date: 2026-06-30
Authors@R: c(
    person("Michael", "Totty", email = "mictott@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-9292-8556")),
    person("Stephanie", "Hicks", role = "aut"),
    person("Boyi", "Guo", role = "aut"))
Description: Spatially aware quality control (QC) for single-cell resolution
    spatial transcriptomics data such as Xenium, CosMx, MERFISH, Stereo-seq,
    Slide-seq, and Visium HD. CellSweeper extends the SpotSweeper framework
    by first clustering cells in gene expression space and then performing
    spatially aware outlier detection within each cluster. A three-level
    pipeline removes obvious debris, identifies entire artifact clusters via
    multivariate pseudobulk outlier detection and spatial dispersion testing,
    and flags within-cluster outlier cells on transcriptomic and
    morphological metrics.
